name: turn into
trans: to change or develop from one thing to another

name: peer
trans: a person of the same age, the same social position, or having the same abilities as other people in a group

name: gifted
trans: having a special ability

name: inquisitiveness
trans: the quality of asking a lot of questions about things

name: assess
trans: to decide the quality or importance of something

name: profoundly
trans: in a way that has a strong effect; extremely

name: recognize
trans: to know someone or something because you have seen or experienced that person or thing before

name: moderately
trans: within a middle range in size, amount, or degree; neither great nor little

name: transfer
trans: to move from one place, person, or position to another, or to cause someone or something to move

name: discipline
trans: training that produces obedience or self-control, often in the form of rules and punishments if these are broken, or the obedience or self-control produced by this training

name: constructive
trans: intended to help someone or improve understanding

name: extraordinary
trans: very unusual and special; different in type or greater in degree than the usual or ordinary

name: enriched
trans: to make someone or something better

name: curriculum
trans: all the courses given in a school, college, etc., or a particular course of study in one subject

name: sophisticated
trans: having an understanding of the world and its ways, so that you are not easily fooled, and having an understanding of people and ideas without making them seem simple

name: interpretation
trans: an explanation or opinion of what something means

name: simultaneous
trans: happening or existing at exactly the same time

name: withdrawal
trans: an act of taking something back, removing something, or moving something back

name: dedicate
trans: to give completely your energy, time, etc. to something

name: remedial
trans: (of an activity) intended to correct or improve something, esp. skills
